FBIS4-57650 "drlat099_r_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-099 Daily Report 19 May 1994 Peru State of Emergency Extended In Cusco State of Emergency Extended In Cusco PY1905202594 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 19 May 94 PY1905202594 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network Spanish BFN [Text] The government has extended the state of emergency until 19 July in the Paruro, Acomayo, Chumbivilcas, Canas, and Canchis Provinces, Cusco Department. Houses may be searched without a warrant and restrictions are imposed on peoples' right to move freely from one place to another and to assemble peacefully. Arrests cannot be made without a warrant issued by a court or by the police unless a criminal is caught red-handed. The supreme decree, published in EL PERUANO, states that the state of exception seeks to expedite antiterrorist operations in that region.
